London Aprll. the 7th 1696
On Satturday last 2 suspected
persons were taken in Barnaby Street
in Southwark the one an Apothecary
the other a Hatter -- -- --
On Sunday a Jacobite Meeting
at a ?? ?? in Newgate street
was disturbed and 12 persons seized and
carryed [carried] before the Justice of Peace
who tendered them the oathis w<sw-ex>hi</sw-ex><sl>ch</sl> they
refusing paid 25<sw-sup>s</sw-sup> a man and were
discharged -- -- --
